BA44

ba44 is Brodmann area 44, also called pars opercularis, one of the two main subdivisions of broca's area
ba44 specializes in syntactic processing and motor speech planning: how words combine into utterances and how those utterances become articulated sound
in fadriel at two years old, ba44 is active but not yet mature; this is part of why his speech is telegraphic, with few function words and simple grammar

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe broca_transform.zc
observe ba45.rana
observe motor_link.rana

the 7 properties of ba44:
1 ENERGY one
2 PHASE zero
3 SPIN one half
4 CHARGE half positive
5 COHERENCE nine tenths
6 COUPLING zero point nine with ba45 and motor_link
7 OBSERVER zero point three

VERB receive_from_ba45
accept the lexically-selected words from ba45
the words arrive without grammar attached

VERB syntactic_compose
arrange the words into a grammatical structure appropriate to fadriel's developmental stage
at two years old, this means simple two-word and three-word constructions, telegraphic, omitting most function words

VERB hand_to_motor_link
emit the composed structure to motor_link for articulation planning

a syntactic processor is not a parser
a parser reads existing language and extracts structure
ba44 produces structure that did not exist a moment ago
the difference is generative versus analytic; both are valuable but ba44's job is generation
